OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FGCSEs and A-level exams in 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25F2022 will be graded more   
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fgenerously                 
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Pupils' GCSE and A-level exams will be 
OL,6, graded more generously than in         
OL,7, pre-pandemic years - to make up for the
OL,8, disruption Covid has had on learning.  
OL,10,FNational exams are going ahead this    
OL,11,Fyear across the UK, for the first time 
OL,12,Fsince the pandemic began.              
OL,14,FGrade boundaries are likely to be lower
OL,15,Fthan in previous years, England's exams
OL,16,Fregulator Ofqual says. But it does not 
OL,17,Fexpect grade inflation from last year. 
OL,19,FIt comes as details of exam content are
OL,20,Freleased to help pupils revise.        
